<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170178>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Morphology of Tyrodes segrex Kurbatov (A, C–F. Male. B. Female). A, B. Dorsal habitus. C. Antennomere 1. D. Meso- and metaventrite and ventral side of abdomen. E. Metaventral projection. F. Lateral side of abdomen. Scale bars: 1.0 mm in A, B; 0.5 mm in D, F; 0.2 mm in E; 0.1 mm in C." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170178/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170184>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Head of Tyrodes segrex Kurbatov (A, C–D. Male. B. Female) in SEM images. A, B. Head in lateral view; C. Posterolateral clypeal region in lateral view; D. Posterolateral clypeal region in dorsal view. Abbreviations: ant1—antennomere 1; mp—maxillary palpus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170184/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170189>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Morphological details of Tyrodes segrex Kurbatov (A–B. Male. C–D. Female) in SEM images. A. Tergite IV. B, C. Abdomen in lateral view. D. Tergite VIII—enlarged image of the dashed white line square in Fig. 2C." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170189/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170193>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Collecting environment and habitat of Tyrodes segrex (A–C. Mt. Iwaki-san, Aomori-ken; D, E. Mt. Kurodake, Ôitaken). A, D. Collecting site. B, C. The moss where T. segrex inhabited. D. The tree T. segrex were walking on." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170193/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170207>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Aedeagus of Tyrodes segrex Kurbatov (A–C) and Tyrodes amamianus sp. nov. (D–F). A, D. Ventral view. B, E. Lateral view. C, F. Dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm in A–F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170207/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

